OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Floyd Bennett Field - Coast Guard Station
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located at the Coast Guard Station on the eastern edge of Floyd Bennett Field in the Jamaica Bay Unit of Gateway National Recreation Area. The station can be found on the USGS 7.5' Coney Island N.Y.-N.J. quadrangle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Island Channel at Floyd Bennet Field
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Island Channel at Floyd Bennet Field. The channel is east of the airfield, and was sampled just south of the pier.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Floyd Bennet Field - East Shoreline Pier
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Floyd Bennet Field east shoreline pier in Island Channel of Jamaica Bay. This is a former remote sensor station. This station is accessed by motor vehicle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located in the middle of Rockaway Inlet between Rockaway Point and Manhattan Beach. The station can be found on the USGS 7.5 minute Coney Island N.Y.-N.J. quadrangle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Rockaway Inlet of Jamaica Bay adjacent to its south shoreline, north of the terminus of approximately Beach 227nd Street of Rockaway. This station is accessed by motor vehicle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Rockaway Inlet - South Shoreline at Low Tide
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Rockaway Inlet of Jamaica Bay adjacent to its south shoreline at low tide, north of the terminus of approximately Beach 227nd Street of Rockaway. This station is accessed by motor vehicle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Jamaica Bay Inlet - Beach Channel Drive
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Jamaica Bay Inlet and Beach Channel Drive, north of the terminus of Beach 149th Street of Rockaway. This station is accessed by motor vehicle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located just off Canarsie Pier in Jamaica Bay. The station can be found on the USGS 7.5' Brooklyn N.Y. quadrangle and can be accessed by car or boat.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located where the Fresh Creek Basin empties into Jamaica Bay opposite the Pennsylvania Avenue Landfill. The station can be found on the USGS 7.5' Brooklyn N.Y. quadrangle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Fresh Creek mouth, near the west bank. This station was accessed by motor vehicle. This was a temporary station, sampled only May 17, 2012.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located at the Old Mill Creek inlet to Jamaica Bay. The station can be found on the USGS 7.5' Jamaica NY quadrangle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Canarsie Pier - center of pier, in Jamaica Bay. The station is accessed by motor vehicle.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Gerritsen Creek, adjacent to Brooklyn Marine Park, near the creek mouth.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Mill Basin, just upstream of Mill Basin Bridge.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Mill Basin at an unnamed tributary. The tributary is on the east bank, just north of the Belt Parkway Bridge. This station is accessed by motor vehicle.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Paerdegat Basin, just upstream of Belt Parkway Bridge.

MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Fresh Creek, near the Belt Parkway Bridge.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
